These household kits will be distributed in a phased manner based on the data of sugarcane harvester beneficiaries in the above mentioned 10 districts and all other districts of the state.
The beneficiary should be a sugarcane farmer and the concerned Gram Sevak should have an identity card / certificate.
In order to avail the benefit, it will be necessary to fill the requisition form in the prescribed format with the Assistant Commissioner, Social Welfare Department.
At the district level, there will be an Assistant Commissioner, Social Welfare Coordinating Officer (Nodal Officer).
The committee headed by the District Collector should include District Social Welfare Officer, Zilla Parishad as well as Assistant Commissioner, Social Welfare, etc.

The e-tendering / GEM system should be adopted from the headquarters level of the Social Justice Department or the corporation regarding the supply of household kits for sugarcane workers and families.
The quality of the item in the home set will need to be checked by a government-approved testing school before the tender for the home set is accepted.
All expenses including supply, transportation, storage, insurance, distribution, photo, manpower supply, etc., except Goods and Services Tax, will be included in the rate of household goods.
It will be necessary to engrave the name of the corporation on the items in the set of household items.

The payments will be made after the selected beneficiary receives the kits, receives a receipt from the Assistant Commissioner, Social Welfare, and after receiving the proposal from the head office of the Corporation for payment of the payment on their recommendation.
It will be mandatory to take a photograph of the sugarcane harvest worker beneficiary while distributing the home kit.
Household kits should be distributed through the office of the Assistant Commissioner, Social Welfare, either by camping or by visiting places during the off-season.
The company which has fixed the process of stocking the household items will be obliged to supply within the prescribed time.
This benefit will be given to only one sugarcane farmer in the family once.

para_trans: Procedure to be followed for supply of household kits: -
This Government decision is available on the website of the Government of Maharashtra www.maharashtra.gov.in.
table_trans: Eligible beneficiaries will be selected through a committee constituted at the district level under the chairmanship of the District Collector, constituted by a Government decision dated 4th August 2021, for supply of the proposed kits of household items.
The beneficiary selection committee shall consist of Assistant Commissioner, Member Secretary Social Welfare and Social Welfare Officer as Zila Parishad member.
Since the corporation does not have a separate district office at the district level, the scheme will be implemented through the Assistant Commissioner, Social Welfare.

In case applications are received in excess of the target set by the Corporation, the beneficiary will be selected through lottery in a committee constituted under the chairmanship of the District Collector.
Benefits of the scheme will be distributed in the form of commodities to the beneficiaries selected by the Beneficiary Selection Committee.
The Assistant Commissioner Social Welfare concerned will be responsible for ensuring that there is no irregularity in the allotment of household items.
